article.headline: Oregon State 82, Birmingham Sou 39
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Casey Nash tied her career high with 26
points on 10 of 12 shooting Sunday in Oregon State's 82-39 win
against Birmingham-Southern.

Ashley Allen added 15 points and nine rebounds for Oregon State
(4-1). Judie Lomax had 12 points and 12 rebounds, her fourth
double-double in the Beavers' first five games.

Keanna Vicks had 10 points to lead Birmingham-Southern (2-6).

Oregon State scored the first 20 points of the game and led
45-17 at halftime. Nash, a senior guard, had 22 points in the first
half, and scored Oregon State's first four points of the second
half to tie her career high in points.

With the game in control, Nash played just three minutes in the
second half. Oregon State's winning margin (43) was its largest of
the game. The Beavers led by as many as 31 in the first half.

Oregon State shot 28 of 56 from the floor, while
Birmingham-Southern was 14 of 48. Oregon State was 23 of 31 at the
free-throw line and Birmingham-Southern was 7 of 12. Oregon State
had the rebounding advantage 44-27, including 15 offensive
rebounds.
